TY  - JOUR
AU  - He, Zhiguo
T1  - Dynamic Compensation Contracts with Private Savings
PY  - 2012
Y1  - 2012/05/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhs054
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 25
IS  - 5
SP  - 1494
EP  - 1549
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - This article studies a dynamic agency problem in which a risk-averse agent can save privately. In the optimal contract, (i) cash compensations exhibit downward rigidity to failures; (ii) permanent pay raises occur when the agent's historical performance is sufficiently good; (iii) and when the agent is dismissed due to poor performance, he walks away with severance pay to support his post-firing consumption at the current compensation level. Thus, the theory can simultaneously explain the popularity of options-like compensation contracts and the increasing incidence of forced turnovers with sizeable severance pay.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhs054
ER  - 



